> the two times I saw higher temps. (I know I should measure by CHT and I will, but this was oil temperature.)

Yes. Oil Temp and CHT are inversely proportional. Higher RPM means
more cooling air over the heads, but faster movement of the engine
parts means higher oil temp, and vice versa.

